<item>
            <title>[LU-10706] Lustre server RPMs for Lustre upgrade</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10706</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In preparation for Lustre upgrade, I&apos;m trying to build the RPMs and wondering if MOFED v4.2 is currently supported in 2.10.3? &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I got the Lustre filesystem mounted but I&apos;m not sure if I&apos;m going to run into any issue later. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am looking at the repo &lt;a href=&quot;https://downloads.hpdd.intel.com/public/lustre/lustre-2.10.3/el7.4.1708/server/RPMS/x86_64/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://downloads.hpdd.intel.com/public/lustre/lustre-2.10.3/el7.4.1708/server/RPMS/x86_64/&lt;/a&gt; but it&apos;s not the kernel that I&apos;m running.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The kernel is Linux gt001 3.10.0-693.17.1.el7.x86_64 #1 SMP Thu Jan 25 20:13:58 UTC 2018 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and MOFED version is &lt;br/&gt;
$ ofed_info -s&lt;br/&gt;
MLNX_OFED_LINUX-4.2-1.2.0.0:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m just going to do this:&lt;br/&gt;
./configure --enable-server \ --with-o2ib=/usr/src/ofa_kernel/default&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
