                            <comment id="221708" author="pjones" created="Mon, 26 Feb 2018 21:26:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Gin&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="221706" author="gtan" created="Mon, 26 Feb 2018 21:20:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yep you may close this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="221664" author="pjones" created="Mon, 26 Feb 2018 14:34:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The lustre.org instructions are meant to be the definitive ones. &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gtan&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;gtan&quot;&gt;gtan&lt;/a&gt; do you have what you need now? Can we close the ticket?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="221639" author="gtan" created="Mon, 26 Feb 2018 05:07:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yep, I was using the patchless and I&apos;ve just built the kernel RPMs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I followed this instruction &lt;a href=&quot;https://wiki.hpdd.intel.com/display/PUB/Building+Lustre+from+Source&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://wiki.hpdd.intel.com/display/PUB/Building+Lustre+from+Source&lt;/a&gt; but it didn&apos;t mention that I need to use&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt; --without kabichk 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;but I found the other instruction here: &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.lustre.org/Compiling_Lustre&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://wiki.lustre.org/Compiling_Lustre&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="221575" author="mdiep" created="Fri, 23 Feb 2018 15:57:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gtan&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;gtan&quot;&gt;gtan&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Your ./configure is fine assuming that you have patched your kernel. If not, please review &lt;a href=&quot;https://wiki.hpdd.intel.com/display/PUB/Building+Lustre+from+Source&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://wiki.hpdd.intel.com/display/PUB/Building+Lustre+from+Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="221563" author="pjones" created="Fri, 23 Feb 2018 13:46:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Gin&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yes MOFED 4.2 is supported with 2.10.3. We built with&#160;MOFED 4.2-1.2.0.0 at the time of the release but I would expect it to be possible to use slight variations on that version without problems.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Minh&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please help provide Gin with any guidance she needs to build successfully&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
